node.text:
His heart was full of love, he was dangerous, he was a guardian, he was always happy to see us and he was one of the few dogs that actually smiled to show us he loved us.
.
I tried really hard to bring him back. I’m gonna miss that smile. Might need a minute. 
.
Thank you to everyone whom showed Rambo love over the years. He loved you back. 
.
No matter what challenges you face, keep going. Take a minute to process, and then put one foot in front of the other knowing how strong you’ll be on the other side of it. 
.
Tough few days for me. Better days ahead. Continuing the journey. 
.
Seriously, everyone that showed him love. Thank you. It meant the world to him. 
.
Stay strong. 🙏🏻

node.text:
13 candles 🎂.
.
Today has me stumped. This one is tough. But I will say this. 
.
I’ve always loved racing. That being said, all the accomplishments, all the race wins, all the Championships, and every goal reached, you were the driving force behind it. None of it would be possible if you weren’t here watching.
.
Why?
.
I wanted you to think I was cool. 
.
Happy Birthday Jaeden 🎂

node.text:
A little bit of insight into my draw method, draw stroke, and stance during an exercise to develop accuracy. 
.
Click the link in my bio and leave your email address for USCCA educational document. Tons of good stuff in there regarding statistics, training methods, and all kinds of intel on defending yourself from a violent attack. Including membership opportunities to prevent you from legal troubles should you have an unfortunate event like I. Being shot at is not fun, surviving a lethal force attack shouldn’t come with secondary legal troubles. Stay protected. 
.
Really proud to be partners with @uscca given their goal to help others stay safe. Especially in today’s world.
.
Going to be doing these a couple times a month. Tag some friends and let me know what else you would like to learn and see. 
.
Thanks for your support everyone. Hope everyone had a great Monday. 
👍🏻🇺🇸
